OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779696396
OL,3,CTemperatures in UK could be hotter
OL,4,Cthan the Seychelles on Saturday
OL,6,FThe current May temperature record is
OL,7,F32.8C, which was logged in Camden
OL,8,FSquare, north London, in 1922, and in
OL,9,FHorsham in West Sussex, Tunbridge
OL,10,FWells in Kent, and Regent's Park in
OL,11,Fcentral London in 1944.
OL,13,FUV levels will also be high across
OL,14,Fmuch of the UK over the bank holiday
OL,15,Fweekend, with a UV index of seven
OL,16,Fexpected in Cardiff and London on
OL,17,FSaturday, as well as in Manchester on
OL,18,FSunday ` meaning anyone enjoying the
OL,19,Foutdoors is advised to apply sun cream.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
